					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Typically the sound engine is called once per frame, and will play the music that is supposed to play by writing to $4000-$400F APU registers.
<br />Most games use all channels for sound FX and music (when there is a SFX the music is temporaly silented on that channel), but some games doesn't use all chanels to simplify code (typically Dragon Quest/Warrior only uses one square and triangle for music and one square and noise for SFX, it also uses the second square for title screen and ending. The same applies to Gradius).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
