					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">clueless wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How much CPU time is typically required to keep a back-ground music track running (ie, keep the "buffer" if you will, saturated)?</div>
<br />There is no buffer. The APU plays waveforms without any CPU help; the CPU just needs to tell it to change parameters (frequency, volume, etc.). Most (all?) music drivers run at a regular rate, usually every frame. During that time, the playback code advance in the music sequence data as necessary and updates waveform parameters.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

