						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It's not a matter of speed, it's just that using the noise channel may not sound as realistic as actual drums. The noise channel produces basically a hissing sound, but if it starts suddenly with a high volume and then slowly fades away, it sounds close to a drum beat.</div>
